            <header>
                <h1>Understanding AWS (Amazon Web Services)</h1>
                <p class="author">By Tanmay Sawankar</p>
            </header>
            <article>
                <section>
                    <h2>Introduction</h2>
                    <div class="blog-flex"> <p>Amazon Web Services (AWS) is a
                            comprehensive and widely adopted cloud platform that
                            offers a plethora of services such as computing
                            power, storage options, and databases to help
                            businesses scale and grow. This blog provides an
                            overview of AWS and its key services, benefits, and
                            how to get started.</p>

                        <img src="img/amazon-blog.png"
                            alt="Blog Logo" class="blog-logo">
                    </div>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Key Services of AWS</h2>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)</h3>
                            <p>Amazon EC2 provides scalable computing capacity
                                in the cloud. It allows users to launch virtual
                                servers as needed, offering flexibility and
                                scalability for various applications.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)</h3>
                            <p>Amazon S3 is an object storage service that
                                offers industry-leading scalability, data
                                availability, security, and performance. It's
                                designed to store and retrieve any amount of
                                data from anywhere on the web.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Amazon RDS (Relational Database Service)</h3>
                            <p>Amazon RDS makes it easy to set up, operate, and
                                scale a relational database in the cloud. It
                                supports several database engines, including
                                MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Oracle, and SQL
                                Server.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Amazon Lambda</h3>
                            <p>AWS Lambda lets you run code without provisioning
                                or managing servers. You pay only for the
                                compute time you consume. It automatically
                                scales your application by running code in
                                response to each trigger.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Amazon VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)</h3>
                            <p>Amazon VPC lets you provision a logically
                                isolated section of the AWS cloud where you can
                                launch AWS resources in a virtual network that
                                you define.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Benefits of AWS</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> AWS provides a wide
                            range of services that can scale up or down based on
                            the needs of your application.</li>
                        <li><strong>Cost-Effectiveness:</strong> AWS offers a
                            pay-as-you-go pricing model, which allows businesses
                            to manage costs efficiently.</li>
                        <li><strong>Security:</strong> AWS provides a secure
                            cloud computing environment, with numerous
                            compliance programs and features to protect your
                            data.</li>
                        <li><strong>Global Reach:</strong> AWS has a vast global
                            infrastructure, enabling businesses to deploy
                            applications in multiple regions worldwide.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Getting Started with AWS</h2>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Create an AWS Account</h3>
                            <p>Sign up for an AWS account at the <a
                                    href="https://aws.amazon.com"
                                    target="_blank">AWS website</a>. You will
                                need a valid credit card for billing
                                purposes.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Set Up the AWS Management Console</h3>
                            <p>The AWS Management Console is a web application
                                that provides access to your AWS services.
                                Navigate to the console and log in with your
                                credentials.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Explore Free Tier Services</h3>
                            <p>AWS offers a free tier that allows you to use
                                some AWS services for free up to certain limits.
                                This is a great way to get hands-on experience
                                with AWS without incurring costs.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Launch Your First EC2 Instance</h3>
                            <p>Follow the step-by-step instructions in the AWS
                                Management Console to launch your first EC2
                                instance. Choose an instance type, configure the
                                instance, and connect to it via SSH.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Learn with AWS Tutorials</h3>
                            <p>AWS provides a wealth of tutorials and
                                documentation to help you learn and build on the
                                platform. Explore the <a
                                    href="https://aws.amazon.com/training/"
                                    target="_blank">AWS Training and
                                    Certification</a> page for more
                                resources.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                    <p>AWS is a powerful and versatile cloud platform that
                        offers a wide range of services to meet the needs of
                        businesses of all sizes. By understanding its key
                        services and benefits, and by getting hands-on
                        experience, you can leverage AWS to build, deploy, and
                        scale your applications efficiently and securely.</p>
                </section>
            </article>
